MEC Albert Fritz says they are assisting a 13-year-old girl who was allegedly raped by a gang of men. CAPE TOWN - Social Development MEC Albert Fritz says they are assisting a 13-year-old girl who was allegedly raped by a gang of men.Police say the girl was abducted by one of them while walking along Robert Sobukwe Road on Friday evening.He took her to his shack in Nyanga where she was allegedly raped repeatedly by him and several others before being released the next day.Fritz says they are assisting to ensure the wellbeing of the 13-year-old girl. We re busy with the case and obviously for certain reasons I cannot make any other comments around that, but we re follow the normal protocol. #NyangaRape Seven young men have already been arrested in connection with her abduction and rape on Friday night.#NyangaRape Police are hunting for an 8th suspect in connection with the gang rape of a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga.The organisation Women and Men against Child Abuse's Ngaa Murombedzi says the teenager is likely to experience an array of emotions. Anger, resentment and maybe she ll blame herself. We re trying to move the children from focusing on blaming herself and focusing on the incident. Seven men between the ages of 18 and 20 are expected to appear in the Wynberg Magistrates Court on Friday, while police are hunting an 8th suspect.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)